requirements.description:
The function `get_attachment_filename` is completely absent from the module.
      Five tests in `TestFilenameExtraction` fail with `AttributeError` because this
      function does not exist.  It is responsible for deriving a local filename from
      a GitHub attachment URL, covering four distinct URL patterns:
      (1) modern assets: github.com/user-attachments/assets/{id}
      (2) modern files: github.com/user-attachments/files/{num}/{name}
      (3) legacy CDN: user-images.githubusercontent.com/{user}/{file}
      (4) private CDN: private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/{user}/{file}?jwt=...
      (5) repo-scoped files: github.com/{owner}/{repo}/files/{num}/{file}
